      \n    \n        \n                                                                                                                                                                                                        \n            \n    \n    \n        \n                \n                    \n                        \n                                    \u003cdiv id=\"article-body\" itemprop=\"articleBody\"\u003e\u003cp\u003eGoogle Messages remains one of the best texting apps on Android. In fact, with RCS on the iPhone, \u003ca href=\"https://www.androidpolice.com/t-mobile-more-rcs-messages-than-other-carriers/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eRCS usage has increased\u003c/a\u003e significantly. Google keeps tweaking the app\u0026#39;s UI, introducing subtle changes now and then. While the company has been experimenting with a \u003ca href=\"https://www.androidpolice.com/google-messages-material-3-expressive-contact-profile/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eMaterial 3 Expressive redesign\u003c/a\u003e, it\u0026#39;s also continuing to refine the UI used by stable users.\u003c/p\u003e            \n    \n                    \n                        \n    \n    \n                                        \n    \n        \n    \n        \n                \n        \n    \u003cdiv data-include-community-rating=\"false\" id=\"0221-4080-91d358c2b6a0\" data-nosnippet=\"\"\u003e\n        \n        \n                        \t\n\t                \n\t\t\u003ca href=\"https://www.androidpolice.com/google-messages-swipe-through-media-items/\"\u003e\n\t\n\t\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/gemini-in-google-messages.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\n\n            \n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\n        \u003cpicture\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/gemini-in-google-messages.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=422\u0026amp;h=268\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/gemini-in-google-messages.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=422\u0026amp;h=268\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                    \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/gemini-in-google-messages.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=310\u0026amp;h=220\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/gemini-in-google-messages.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=310\u0026amp;h=220\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                    \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/gemini-in-google-messages.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=720\u0026amp;h=400\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/gemini-in-google-messages.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=720\u0026amp;h=400\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                    \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/gemini-in-google-messages.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=432\u0026amp;h=260\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/gemini-in-google-messages.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=432\u0026amp;h=260\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                    \n                    \u003cimg width=\"5184\" height=\"2916\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"Gemini integration in Google Messages\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/gemini-in-google-messages.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/12/gemini-in-google-messages.jpg\"/\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/picture\u003e\n                \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\t\t\u003c/a\u003e\n\t\n\n        \n                    \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan data-field=\"label\"\u003eRelated\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n                \n        \n        \n        \n            \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIn June, Google rolled out a UI change in Messages that \u003ca href=\"https://www.androidpolice.com/google-messages-new-gallery-camera-interface/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003ecombined the camera and gallery\u003c/a\u003e buttons into one. Tapping it opened a new view with the camera feed on top and recent gallery photos below. Users could swipe up to access their full gallery, but the change made the process more cumbersome.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003cp\u003eMany on social media \u003ca href=\"https://www.reddit.com/r/AndroidQuestions/comments/1l4lffv/google_messages_now_opens_your_camera_everytime/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"\u003ecriticized this layout\u003c/a\u003e â€” some didn\u0026#39;t want to \u003ca href=\"https://www.reddit.com/r/AndroidQuestions/comments/1l4lffv/comment/mwjcq2j/?utm_source=share\u0026amp;utm_medium=web3x\u0026amp;utm_name=web3xcss\u0026amp;utm_term=1\u0026amp;utm_content=share_button\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"\u003esee the camera every time\u003c/a\u003e, while others found accessing the gallery had become a two-step task.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003ch2 id=\"google-messages-just-undid-one-of-its-most-annoying-ui-changes\"\u003e\n                        Google Messages just undid one of its most annoying UI changes\n               \u003c/h2\u003e\n    \n    \n    \n\u003cp\u003eThankfully, Google has responded to user feedback and is reportedly reverting to the old layout with separate buttons for camera and gallery. Some Reddit users report that tapping the \u0026#39;+\u0026#39; icon in a chat now shows two distinct buttons for \u0026#39;Camera\u0026#39; and \u0026#39;Gallery\u0026#39; (via \u003ca href=\"https://9to5google.com/2025/07/14/google-messages-gallery-camera-standalone/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e9to5Google\u003c/a\u003e).\u003c/p\u003e    \u003cp\u003eAs before, these appear first in the action tray before options like GIFs, Stickers, and Magic Compose.\u003c/p\u003e            \n    \n                    \n                        \n    \n    \n                                        \n    \n        \n    \n        \n                \n        \n    \u003cdiv data-include-community-rating=\"false\" id=\"dd16-42e8-91445e6fd6a9\" data-nosnippet=\"\"\u003e\n        \n        \n                        \t\n\t                \n\t\t\u003ca href=\"https://www.androidpolice.com/google-is-sprucing-up-messages-search-interface/\"\u003e\n\t\n\t\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/google-messages-2-ap24-hero.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\n\n            \n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\n        \u003cpicture\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/google-messages-2-ap24-hero.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=422\u0026amp;h=268\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/google-messages-2-ap24-hero.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=422\u0026amp;h=268\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                    \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/google-messages-2-ap24-hero.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=310\u0026amp;h=220\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/google-messages-2-ap24-hero.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=310\u0026amp;h=220\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                    \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/google-messages-2-ap24-hero.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=720\u0026amp;h=400\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/google-messages-2-ap24-hero.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=720\u0026amp;h=400\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                    \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/google-messages-2-ap24-hero.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=432\u0026amp;h=260\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/google-messages-2-ap24-hero.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=432\u0026amp;h=260\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                    \n                    \u003cimg width=\"2560\" height=\"1440\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"The words \u0026#39;Google Messages\u0026#39; against a blue and light green background\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/google-messages-2-ap24-hero.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/google-messages-2-ap24-hero.jpg\"/\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/picture\u003e\n                \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\t\t\u003c/a\u003e\n\t\n\n        \n                    \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan data-field=\"label\"\u003eRelated\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n                \n        \n        \n        \n            \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe combined camera/gallery shortcut still exists but now sits in the text field next to the emoji icon, for those who prefer the new UI. But, at least now, users have a choice.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003cp\u003eThe change doesn\u0026#39;t appear to be rolling out widely yet. I don\u0026#39;t see the new UI on \u003ca href=\"https://www.androidpolice.com/google-pixel-9-one-year-later-experience/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003emy Google Pixel 9\u003c/a\u003e, even on the latest Messages beta (version 20250713). It\u0026#39;s possible Google is still testing the UI again based on user feedback. If the rollout expands, we\u0026#39;ll keep you posted.\u003c/p\u003e    \n    \n    \n    \n\u003c/div\u003e\n    \n                \n        \n        \n\n\n        \n\n\n\n\n\n                                            \n\n\n\n\n        \n    \u003c/article\u003e\n\n    \n            \n        \u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
